<h2 class="nounderline">Featured Publication</h2>

<p>I am the author of a book, Wordjazz for Stevie, which is  a personal account of the eight years I spent looking after my profoundly  disabled daughter - in addition to her Down syndrome she suffered brain damage  that left her blind, profoundly handicapped and epileptic. The book has just  been released in the USA November 2010. See <a href="http://www.blacksmithbooks.com/9789881774279.htm" target="_blank">www.blacksmithbooks.com</a> for further details.<br />
  &nbsp;<br />
  The birth of Stevie led to my founding the Hong Kong Down  Syndrome Association (now a leading Hong Kong charity) and co-founding Mental  Handicap Network China which was a catalyst for taking family centred  approaches into China where we established the Yang Ai Centre in Guangzhou &ndash;  and established an annual conference in that city attended by several hundred  interested parties from many distant parts of China.<br />
  &nbsp;<br />
  Thank you<br />
  &nbsp;<br />
  Jonathan Chamberlain</p>
